那三胞胎不算是我的 所以你就想要抛弃他们！

165
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:08,930
Oh, no, I would never do that. No. I just..
噢，不！我永远不会那么做。不。

166
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:13,730
was thinking that, you know, maybe you could take one.
我只是想，你知道吗 也许你可以带走一个。

167
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,600
What?
什么？！  

168
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:20,110
You can't separate them, that's terrible! Which one?
你不能把它们分开！这太可怕了。 哪一个？

169
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,640
Thank you so much for seeing us.
谢谢你能让我们来。

170
00:10:26,820 --> 00:10:29,020
Phoebe has told us great things about you guys.
菲比跟我们说过你们做的好事了。

171
00:10:29,190 --> 00:10:30,820
Please, we're happy to help.
噢，请进，我们很愿意帮忙。

172
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:33,620
We went through the same thing when we were adopting.
我们领养的时候也经历过这种事

173
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:37,890
So a lot of malfunctioning wee-wees and hoo-hoos in this room, huh?
那么，这间屋子里也充斥着 wee-wee和hoo-hoo的故障声了，呃？

174
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,530
I mean, you have a lovely home.
我是说，你们过得很开心。

175
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:49,010
We appreciate anything you can tell us.
好吧，你们说的一切我们都很感激。

176
00:10:49,180 --> 00:10:52,630
Well, actually, I think this might help.
当然，实际上，我想会有帮助的。

177
00:10:52,850 --> 00:10:53,870
It's pretty much..
这些大概就是

178
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:56,210
- all the information you need. - Oh, my God.
-你们所需要的所有信息了。 -噢，天呐！

179
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:59,220
Everything is broken into categories, then cross-referenced.
所有的东西都按类别分开 可以互相引用

180
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:02,220
Then color-coded to correspond with the forms in the back.
还根据背面的颜色进行了标注。

181
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:03,520
Thank you.
太感谢了。

182
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:06,020
I think I just had a tiny orgasm.
我想我刚经历了一次小高潮。

183
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:13,670
I know the process is frustrating, but it's so worth it.
我知道过程是让人沮丧的 不过是值得的。

184
00:11:13,830 --> 00:11:16,890
Adopting Owen was the best thing that ever happened to us.
领养欧文是我们经历过得最好的事情。

185
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:19,330
That's great. Can I see the book?
太棒了。我能看看这本书吗？

186
00:11:20,540 --> 00:11:23,600
You want me to wash my hands first, don't you?
你想让我先洗手，是不是？

187
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,840
Please. It's just so pretty and white.
这……这个这么漂亮，而且是白的。

188
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,180
Bathroom is down the hall to your left.
洗手间在走廊那头，左边。

189
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:32,950
I would have told him to do it too.
我也让他这么做过。

190
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:35,250
Can I adopt you?
我能领养你吗?

191
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:39,720
- Hey, you must be Owen. - Yeah.
-嗨，你一定是欧文。 -对。

192
00:11:39,930 --> 00:11:42,450
I'm Chandler. Hey, I was in the Scouts too.
我叫钱德。嗨，我也当过童子军。

193
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:46,230
- You were? - In fact, my father was a den mother.
-真的？ -当然，实际上我爸爸是童子军的女训导员。

194
00:11:48,070 --> 00:11:49,900
You know how to use a compass?
你知道怎么用指南针吗？

195
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:51,640
I have a badge in it.
我得过一枚徽章。

196
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,070
- You do? That's fantastic. - You want to see it?
-真的？真是太棒了！ -你想看吗？

197
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,640
I'd love to, but I gotta get back to your parents.
当然想，不过我得先回去跟你的父母聊聊。

198
00:11:56,810 --> 00:11:59,110
They're telling us about how they adopted you.
他们在告诉我们怎么领养你的事。

199
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:00,910
What?
什么？！？

200
00:12:06,950 --> 00:12:08,720
What?
怎么了？

201
00:12:09,590 --> 00:12:12,150
I'm adopted?
我是领养的？

202
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:15,450
I got nothing.
我什么都不知道。

203
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,860
I'm adopted?
我是领养的？

204
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:24,140
No.
不

205
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:27,230
I didn't say that. I said..
我没那么说. 我是说..

206
00:12:27,410 --> 00:12:29,740
you're a doctor.
你是个医生.

207
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,500
A doctor.
一个医生.

208
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:37,050
Hey, doctor, my arm hurts. Can you fix it for me?
嗨, 大夫，我的胳膊疼. 你能帮我修理一下吗?

209
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,680
I can't believe I'm adopted.
我真不敢相信我是领养的.

210
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:43,880
So you're not gonna fix my arm?
那..你不准备修理我的胳膊了?

211
00:12:49,230 --> 00:12:53,390
Well, that first batch of margaritas was not so great..
第一批马格丽塔不是太好

212
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:57,000
but this second batch is good.
可第二批实在太棒..棒了。

213
00:12:58,710 --> 00:13:02,040
Well, maybe the next batch, we could all get some.
好吧，希望到下一批的时候 我们都能喝一点。

214
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:04,610
Oh, God, this is fun, isn't it?
噢，伙计们，这很有趣，是吗？

215
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:07,040
You know, just the four of us.
知道吗？就我们四个。

216
00:13:07,210 --> 00:13:09,050
Just hanging.
就这么呆着。

217
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:11,180
Dude, are you okay?
伙计，你还好吧？

218
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:13,290
And when are the fajitas gonna be ready?
法加它什么时候才能好？

219
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:17,810
I'm fine, okay? I'm great.
我很好！嘿，我很棒！

220
00:13:17,990 --> 00:13:20,960
I'm just.. I'm just proud of us.
我只是…… 我只是为我们而骄傲。

221
00:13:21,130 --> 00:13:24,560
You know? There's no weirdness, no tension.
一点都不古怪，一点都不紧张。

222
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:26,760
No awareness.
一点都不清醒。

223
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,870
We make a great foursome. We should do more stuff together.
我们组成一个“四人组”。 我们应该一块再做些什么。

224
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:33,740
Let's take a trip!
哦！ 我们去旅行吧！

225
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,240
We could all go on your boat.
我们可以坐你的船去.

226
00:13:37,410 --> 00:13:40,210
Joey has this amazing sailboat.
乔伊有一艘很棒的帆船.

227
00:13:40,380 --> 00:13:42,710
Actually, Ross, I sold the boat two years ago.
实际上, 罗斯 我两年前我已经把船卖掉了.

228
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,980
Oh, no. Idiot!
哦, 不. 白痴!

229
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:48,690
Well, yeah, but I could get another one.
呃, 是的, 不过我可以弄来另外一个.

230
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:51,450
- This trip sounds great. - Yeah?
- 这个旅行听起来棒极了. - 是吗?

231
00:13:51,630 --> 00:13:54,320
Okay, where do you think we can go?
好, 你觉得我们能去哪?

232
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,730
My fajitas!
我的法加它!!

233
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:02,590
Look, Charlie, I just want you to know..
听着，查莉，我只想让你知道。

234
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:06,870
Ross is just having a little trouble adjusting to the thought of Joey and me.
罗斯还需要时间习惯我跟乔伊在一起。

235
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,270
You know, he normally doesn't drink like this.
知道么，他一般不这么喝酒的。

236
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:12,740
You know what, this is nothing. My father is a raging alcoholic.
噢，你知道吗？这没什么。 我爸爸就是个疯狂的酒鬼。

237
00:14:16,450 --> 00:14:19,110
I'm sorry, have I made this evening uncomfortable?
噢，对不起 让你们不舒服了？

238
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:25,690
Fajitas! Be careful! Very hot plate! Very hot!
法加它!  当心，盘子很烫，盘子很烫！！

239
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:27,850
Ross, you don't even have oven mitts on.
罗斯，你怎么没戴手套！

240
00:14:31,430 --> 00:14:34,200
That is gonna hurt tomorrow.
明天手要疼了！

241
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,690
Okay, well, this is crazy.
好吧，好吧，这太疯狂了。

242
00:14:38,910 --> 00:14:42,400
We can't seriously be talking about me taking one of your kids, can we?
我们不可能是在严肃的讨论 我要带走一个孩子，是吗？

243
00:14:42,580 --> 00:14:44,130
Oh, no, of course we're not.
不，当然不是。

244
00:14:44,310 --> 00:14:45,970
- That's insane. - I know.
- 太愚蠢了。 - 我知道。

245
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:47,610
Alice would never go for it.
爱丽丝不会支持的，是吗？

246
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:51,050
She's pretty tired too. I think we could get her on board.
噢，我不知道，她也太累了。 我想她可能会入伙的。

247
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:57,090
Well, just for argument's sake, you know, hypothetically..
好吧，知道吗，只是为了争论， 知道吗，是假设的。

248
00:14:57,260 --> 00:14:59,350
which one would you be willing to give up?
你要放弃哪一个？

249
00:15:01,460 --> 00:15:02,950
Frank Jr. Jr.?
小小弗兰克?

250
00:15:03,130 --> 00:15:05,360
Well, it'd be great for my shoulder.
噢，你选了这么好的一个。

251
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:07,190
You'd be getting a really good one.
噢，你选了这么好的一个。

252
00:15:07,370 --> 00:15:08,670
He's really funny.
我是说，知道吗，他真是太有趣了。

253
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:11,100
Like, the other day, he made up this joke:
比如，那天他说了个笑话

254
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:13,930
What's green and says, "Hey, I'm a frog"?
什么东西是绿的并且说 “嗨，我是一只青蛙”？

255
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:17,500
A talking frog.
一只会说话的青蛙！

256
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:22,950
Oh, no, you can't have him, he's too funny.
噢，不，你不能带他走。他太有意思了。

257
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:26,650
Well, all right, that's fine. What about Leslie?
好吧，好吧，没问题。那莱丝莉呢？

258
00:15:26,850 --> 00:15:28,980
Oh, no, no, not Leslie. No.
噢，不，不。不要是莱丝莉。

259
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:32,850
She's the only one that knows how to burp the alphabet.
不，她……她是唯一一个会 打着嗝说出字母表来的。

260
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:35,890
All right, so that leaves Chandler.
好吧，那就剩下钱德了。

261
00:15:36,130 --> 00:15:39,330
No, no, you can't have Chandler. No, no. She's my little genius.
噢，不，不，你不能带走钱德 不。不，不。她是个小天才。

262
00:15:39,530 --> 00:15:41,000
I got big hopes for her.
我对她抱有很大期望。

263
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:44,900
She's gonna be a doctor or a realtor.
她会成为医生或者房地产经纪人……

264
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:51,410
Wow, Frank, I think we just ran out of kids.
哇，弗兰克。我想我谁都带不走了。

265
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,670
Oh, I think you're right.
噢，我想你是对的。

266
00:15:57,650 --> 00:16:02,320
Oh, wow. Phoebe, I don't think I can give one of them up.
哦，哇，菲比 我不认为我能放弃任何一个。

267
00:16:02,490 --> 00:16:06,220
I mean, you know, they drive me crazy, but they're my babies.
我是说，知道吗 他们让我发疯，可他们是我的孩子。

268
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:12,030
I'm sorry, Frank, I didn't realize things were so bad.
很抱歉，弗兰克。我没想到事情会这样。

269
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:15,430
You know, I'll help out more. I can baby-sit anytime you want.
知道吗，我会帮你的。 你需要的时候我可以照顾他们。

270
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:17,260
You name the day and I'll be there.
你说一天，我会去的。

271
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,840
- How about tomorrow? - Well, that's not good.
-明天怎么样？ -呃，不好。

272
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:23,940
But I can move some stuff around and I'll be there.
不过知道吗，我会推掉其它事 我会到的。

273
00:16:24,140 --> 00:16:26,310
You and Alice just take the whole day together.
你和爱丽丝可以整天呆在一起。

274
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:28,510
You'd do that for us?
你为我们这么做？

275
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,950
Are you kidding? That's what sisters are for.
你开玩笑吗？你以为姐姐是干什么的？

276
00:16:36,990 --> 00:16:39,360
Oh, look at them.
看看他们！ 

277
00:16:40,430 --> 00:16:43,260
I love you so much.
噢，我真爱你们。

278
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:47,060
Oh, crap, don't wake up! Don't wake up!
噢，天呐，别醒过来，别醒过来！

279
00:16:49,970 --> 00:16:53,100
- Where are Bill and Colleen? - Kitchen, getting something to eat.
-比尔和克琳呢？ -他们在厨房弄点吃的。

280
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:54,800
Can you believe how nice they are?
您能想象他们有多好吗？

281
00:16:54,980 --> 00:16:56,310
We have to leave.
我们必须走！！

282
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:00,880
Why? What did you do in the bathroom?
为什么？你在洗手间做了什么？

283
00:17:01,050 --> 00:17:03,880
I didn't get to the bathroom. I bumped into Owen on the way.
我还没去洗手间呢。 我在路上碰到了欧文

284
00:17:04,050 --> 00:17:06,780
He didn't know he was adopted. There's a slight chance..
可他还不知道他是被领养的。 有一个小小的机会 

285
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:08,320
I may have told him.
我告诉了他。

286
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:12,020
Oh, my God, where's my purse? No, I can replace everything in there.
噢，天呐，我的手袋呢？ 不，我们把东西放在这儿。

287
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:14,630
- Get that binder and let's go! - Hi.
- 拿上活页册，走！ -嗨。

288
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:17,330
Some little snacks for everybody.
给大家的一点小吃。

289
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:20,490
You don't have to eat the sour worms. Those are for Owen.
哦，你们不用吃酸蠕虫， 那是给欧文的。

290
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:22,560
I'll go get him in a second.
我一会儿去叫他。

291
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:26,070
By the way, you should know, we haven't told him he's adopted yet.
顺便说一句， 你们该知道 我们还没告诉他他是领养的。

292
00:17:26,810 --> 00:17:28,930
But kids are so intuitive.
可孩子们直觉很灵敏。

293
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:31,440
Don't you think, on some level, he already knows?
你不认为某种程度上他已经知道了？

294
00:17:31,650 --> 00:17:34,980
- I'm adopted? - See? Intuitive.
- 我是领养的？！ - 看？直觉！

295
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,510
What? Where did you hear that?
什么？你从哪儿听来的？

296
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:38,840
He told me.
他告诉我的！

297
00:17:40,490 --> 00:17:44,010
And he paid me 50 dollars not to tell.
他还给我50块钱让我别说出来。

298
00:17:44,630 --> 00:17:47,250
Which, technically, now you should give back.
那现在你该把钱还给我了！

299
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:52,230
You told him he's adopted?
你告诉他他是领养的？

300
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:55,030
I'm sorry. You should have a sign out there or something.
实在对不起，可你们应该在 那儿或者什么地方写明白。

301
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,360
Or at least whisper it to people when they come in the door.
或者在人们进门的时候悄悄告诉他们：

302
00:17:58,540 --> 00:18:02,030
"Owen doesn't know he's adopted, and he also thinks Santa is real."
“欧文不知道他是领养的， 他也认为圣诞老人是真实存在的。”

303
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,010
He isn't?
他不是吗？！

304
00:18:05,180 --> 00:18:07,550
We have to get out of here, baby.
我们必须走了，亲爱的！

305
00:18:09,050 --> 00:18:10,410
What is the matter with you?
你怎么了？

306
00:18:10,580 --> 00:18:13,640
All right, look, I know what Chandler did was not the best..
好了, 听着, 我知道 钱德做的不是最好的..

307
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:17,720
but anyone would assume that a 12-year-old has been told he's adopted.
但是任何人都应该想到 一个12岁的孩子会被告知是被领养的

308
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:21,450
- Yeah, he's 8. - Wow, he's tall.
- 是的, 他8岁. - 喔, 他长的好高.

309
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:23,450
What country did you get him from?
你从哪个国家领到他的?

310
00:18:26,430 --> 00:18:29,960
Everyone, I would like to make a toast..
诸位，我要向

311
00:18:30,170 --> 00:18:33,070
to Rachel and Joey.
瑞秋和乔伊敬酒。

312
00:18:35,110 --> 00:18:38,100
And to love.
还有爱情。

313
00:18:40,810 --> 00:18:42,180
Ah, love!
啊，爱情。

314
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,550
L-O-V-E. Love.
L-O-V-E，爱情。

315
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,850
L is for "life."
L是生活。

316
00:18:49,020 --> 00:18:51,620
And what is life without love?
没有爱情哪有生活？

317
00:18:52,630 --> 00:18:55,220
Oh, my God, are we supposed to answer?
噢，我的天呐，我们要回答吗？

318
00:18:56,730 --> 00:19:00,000
O is for:
O是

319
00:19:00,970 --> 00:19:03,130
"Oh, wow!"
“噢，哇！”

320
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:09,630
The V is for this..
V是

321
00:19:09,810 --> 00:19:13,800
very surprising turn of events..
事情转变的这么快

322
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:17,680
which I am still fine with, by the way.
而顺便说明，我完全应付得来。

323
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:21,540
E..
E是

324
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:26,160
is for how..
